Which comando (e.g. which bash) >> localiza el comando


alias:
ll >> more details on folders and files

alias is a shortcut

to go back on additional files>>
../../;cat pp.txt

variable de entorno:
$PWD

env >> shows environment

cd / >> goes to root directory

when you open a file you get something like this:

- rw - rw - r -- 1 dsc 18 nov 17:11
r: read
x: execute
w: write
1: # of links (soft and hard)
dsc: owner name
18: byte size
nov 17:11: date modified


